---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import Math from '../components/Math.astro'
import { sourceFile } from '../data/site'
---

<BaseLayout title="Fefferman–Graham Geometry">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <div class="site-shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Fefferman–Graham Geometry</p>

      <h1>Normal form, Ricci equations, finite jets, and obstruction data.</h1>

      <p>
        The FG layer organizes normal-form ambient metric components and the
        formal Ricci-recursion structures that support later geometric
        constructions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="site-shell grid-2">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Normal-Form Metric Components</h3>

        <Math
          display
          tex="\widetilde g=2\rho\,dt^2+2t\,dt\,d\rho+t^2g_{ij}(x,\rho)\,dx^i dx^j"
        />

        <p>
          The implementation records a component-level normal-form model,
          including the inverse metric and coordinate-index decomposition.
        </p>

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/FG/NormalForm.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open NormalForm.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Commutator Infrastructure</h3>

        <Math
          display
          tex="\widetilde\Delta(Qf)=Q\widetilde\Delta f+2(2Xf+(n+2)f)"
        />

        <p>
          These relations connect the defining function, homogeneity operator,
          and ambient Laplacian used by tangentiality arguments.
        </p>

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/FG/Commutators.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open Commutators.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Ricci Normal Form</h3>

        <Math
          display
          tex="\widetilde{\operatorname{Ric}}_{ij}=\rho g''_{ij}-\rho(g'g^{-1}g')_{ij}+\cdots+\operatorname{Ric}(g_\rho)_{ij}"
        />

        <p>
          Symbolic Ricci component equations are stored together with
          certificate interfaces for base-base, base-infinity, and
          infinity-infinity components.
        </p>

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/FG/RicciNormalForm.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open RicciNormalForm.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Finite Jets and Obstruction</h3>

        <Math display tex="g_\rho=g+\rho g^{(1)}+\cdots+\rho^K g^{(K)}" />

        <Math display tex="g^{(1)}=2P" />

        <p>
          Finite metric jets, Ricci recursion data, and an even-dimensional
          obstruction scaffold are prepared for later finite-order existence
          theorems.
        </p>

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/FG/FormalJets.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open FormalJets.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section border-top">
    <div class="site-shell">
      <div class="note">
        The current FG layer provides formal normal-form data, symbolic Ricci
        equations, and finite-recursion interfaces. It does not claim a
        completed tensor-calculus derivation of every certificate field.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>